{{Quote|Not all the Moffs are pleased I am Emperor, Veed especially. They are gravel maggots waiting to feed.|Darth Krayt to Darth Wyyrlok|<ref name="Legacy (2006) 1">[[Legacy (2006) 1|''Legacy'' (2006) 1]]</ref>}}
'''Gravel-maggots''' were worms found in the badlands of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]. They were known to feed on rotting flesh of other creatures. Despite the obscurity of Tatooine, gravel-maggots were infamous throughout the galaxy, and it was a common if uncreative insult to call someone "gravel-maggot" or the "son of a gravel-maggot."<ref name="Trail">[[Granta Omega]], disguised as [[Hunti Pereg]], uses "son of a gravel-maggot" in ''[[Jedi Quest: The Trail of the Jedi]]''.</ref>

